article.headline: Akron 83, Bowling Green 62
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Nate Linhart and Quade Milum each had 16 points and three other Akron players reached double-digits as the Zips defeated Bowling Green 83-62 on Sunday. Cedrick Middleton had 15 points, Romeo Travis added 12 and Dru Joyce had 10 for Akron (11-4, 2-1 Mid-American Conference). The score was tied at 40 early in the second half, but a 3-pointer by Linhart started a 15-4 run that gave the Zips a 55-44 lead with 12:22 left. Akron's lead never dipped below double-digits for the rest of the game. Martin Samarco scored 20 points to lead the Falcons (10-6, 1-2), and Nate Miller added 15 points and seven rebounds. Ryne Hamblet had 10 assists. Travis and Linhart each had seven rebounds for the Zips, who shot 48.4 percent (30-of-62), compared with the Falcons' 46.4 percent (26-of-56). Akron outrebounded Bowling Green 39-30.
